snippet.textDisplay: The thing about flipping only when the underside has colour is a myth that's long been debunked. You can turn the steak as quick as 30 seconds, and as long as you continuously flip every 30 seconds, it will still come out perfect. Flipping often gives you more control over the colour and doneness.

snippet.textDisplay:
Tip #9 is not a good one. Every person has different flesh density (A bodybuilder's forearm will not feel the same as the arm of a 140lb person) and meat will have different pushback/bounce depending on breed (Like Wagyu vs. Angus) and quality of meat (Think Prime vs. Choice vs. Select)

Use a damn meat thermometer, it's the 21st century ffs
